The paper presents a novel neural network architecture for processing sequences, specifically for language modelling and machine translation tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The use of neural networks for sequence processing and language tasks also suggests a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the network in terms of linear time complexity, which suggests a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning).
